  <h3>Information for Members</h3>

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "What if I'm going to be late to co-op?", name: "late") %></h4>
  We understand that last-minute emergencies happen. If you find that you're going to be late (even if just a few minutes late), please call or text our volunteer coordinator at <strong>513-970-CUCO (2826)</strong> by 9:30, preferably before. The sooner we know you won't be there, the easier it will be to cover your position.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "What if I unexpectedly can't make it to co-op?", name: "cannot_make_it") %></h4>
  If you can't make it to co-op please post to the CUCO Google group as soon as possible. If it's co-op day when you realize you can't come, please call or text <strong>513-970-CUCO (2826)</strong> by 9:30, preferably before. Our volunteer coordinators will be working hard to make sure all positions are covered, so the sooner we know you won't be there, the easier it will be to cover your position.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "Does CUCO close for weather emergencies?", name: "weather_emergencies") %></h4>
  If Columbus city schools are closed due to weather, CUCO will be closed. We do not make up classes that are missed due to weather or other extenuating circumstances and we do not offer refunds for missed classes.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "Does CUCO close for any other reason?", name: "cuco_close") %></h4>
  Sometimes there are extenuating circumstances requiring that CUCO is closed unexpectedly. We'll do our best to notify members in a timely manner, as soon as we find out about the need for closing. We do not make up classes that are missed due to weather or other extenuating circumstances and we do not offer refunds for missed classes.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "If CUCO is closed due to weather or other circumstances, will we make up the missed class?", name: "make_up") %></h4>
  No, we will not make up the missed class and we can not offer refunds for the missed class. We will do our best to notify members of unexpected closures in a timely manner, but we do not have the scheduling and financial flexibility to do make-ups or refunds at this time.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "How do I pay my class fees?", name: "pay_fees") %></h4>
  <p>See the <%= link_to "calendar", calendar_path %> to find out when payment is due. You can also check how much you owe by looking at your family schedule. You can pay your fees by cash or check made out to CUCO to our treasurer who you can contact through <%= mail_to "fees@columbusunschoolers.com" %> or through PayPal.</p>
  <p>You can make arrangements with the treasurer to pay early or if something comes up that makes it impossible for you to pay. Any member who doesn't pay their class fees by the due date will be dropped from the classes that require a fee and put into free play.</p>
  <p>If you have a sudden emergency and can not pay by the deadline, please contact the treasurer before the deadline to make other arrangements. If we don't hear from you, we have to assume you're not paying your class fees and we'll have to drop you from your classes.</p>

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "I'm a teacher who is charging a class fee. How do I collect the money from my students?", name: "collect_fees") %></h4>
  Our treasurer will pay you any class fees on the first day of classes. If you need the money to purchase supplies before classes start, contact the treasurer at <%= mail_to "fees@columbusunschoolers.com" %>. They will be happy to make arrangements with you to get the money sooner.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "Why are classes so expensive?", name: "expensive") %></h4>
  Some of our classes have fees in order to cover the cost of supplies. Some of our classes have fees because they are taught by professionals who require payment. Ideally, our classes would all be free but classes are limited to what our members offer.

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "What if I have a concern or issue with someone or something at CUCO?", name: "concern") %></h4>
  <p>After someone has filled out a concern form and it's been determined there should be a meeting to resolve the concern the steps below will be taken.</p>
  <p>The goal of this meeting process is finding a solution to the problem. The Board will hold a meeting in a private comfortable neutral place with cookies. The rules for our meeting will be; no name-calling, everyone takes turns talking, no interrupting, and everything is private and confidential. One Board member will take notes which will be archived on the website for Board members viewing only. A copy will be given to all participants involved.</p>
  <p>See the <%= link_to "Concern Resolution Meeting Process", page_path("concern-process") %> page for more info.</p>

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "What if I can't volunteer due to time and/or other obligations?", name: "hardship") %></h4>
  <p>A hardship pass allows you to be exempt from volunteer jobs for one session. You can request a hardship pass if you have been a member for three or more sessions, you are facing an unusual amount of stressors in your life, and you are unable to contribute by doing any volunteer jobs.</p>
  <p>See the <%= link_to "Hardship Pass", page_path("hardship-pass") %> page for more info.</p>

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "Can I bring a family member who is not signed up?", name: "family") %></h4>
  <p>Yes, whether it's a visiting adult family member, or a kid who is normally in school but has the day off, feel free to bring them. They are welcome to attend drop-in classes, or hang out in free play. Please add them on the website if they will start coming regularly so we can have an idea of who is in the building in case of emergency.</p>

  <h4><%= content_tag(:a, "Can I invite friends who might be interested in co-op to come to parties or to visit for the day?", name: "visitors") %></h4>
  <p>Prospective members are welcome to visit and/or join us at our parties. Please have them contact <%= mail_to "help@columbusunschoolers.com" %> so that we can get them onto our notification list and make sure they're getting accurate information about policies and dates.</p>
<% end %>
